---
export const prerender = true;
import Legal from '../../layouts/Legal.astro';
---

<Legal 
  title="Data Processing Agreement (DPA)" 
  description="Data Processing Agreement pursuant to Article 28 of GDPR (EU) 2016/679 for Passr customers.">
  
  <div class="legal-meta-bar">
    LAST UPDATED: APRIL 24, 2026
  </div>

  <h1>Data Processing Agreement (DPA)</h1>
  <p class="font-mono text-xs text-metal uppercase tracking-widest -mt-4 mb-8">
    Pursuant to Article 28 of GDPR (EU) 2016/679
  </p>

  <div style="background: var(--surface-light-2); padding: 24px; border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1); margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-void);">
      <strong>PREAMBLE:</strong> This Data Processing Agreement ("DPA") forms part of the Terms of Service between the Customer (Data Controller) and Hisako Technologies OÜ / Passr (Data Processor). It governs the processing of personal data by Passr on behalf of the Customer to ensure compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Definitions</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Term</th>
        <th>Definition</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Data Controller</td>
        <td>The Customer (the outdoor brand or business entity using Passr).</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Data Processor</td>
        <td>Passr / Hisako Technologies OÜ.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Personal Data</td>
        <td>Any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person (Art. 4(1) GDPR).</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Processing</td>
        <td>Any operation performed on personal data, such as collection, storage, or disclosure (Art. 4(2) GDPR).</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Sub-processor</td>
        <td>Any third party engaged by Passr to process personal data on behalf of the Customer.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>2. Subject Matter and Duration</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Subject:</strong> The subject matter of this DPA is the processing of personal data necessary to provide the Passr Digital Product Passport platform and related compliance services.</li>
    <li><strong>Duration:</strong> This DPA remains in effect for the duration of the Customer's active subscription to the Passr platform.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Nature and Purpose of Processing</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Category</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Legal Basis</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Brand Admin User Data</td>
        <td>Account management, secure authentication</td>
        <td>Contract Performance</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Brand Team User Data</td>
        <td>Access control and collaborative editing</td>
        <td>Contract Performance</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Passport Scan Events</td>
        <td>Analytics reporting for the Customer</td>
        <td>Legitimate Interest</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>4. Technical and Organisational Measures (TOMs)</h2>
  <p>
    Passr implements the following state-of-the-art security measures to protect personal data:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Encryption in Transit:</strong> Mandatory TLS 1.3 encryption for all data transmissions.</li>
    <li><strong>Encryption at Rest:</strong> AES-256 encryption for all database volumes and backups.</li>
    <li><strong>Access Control:</strong> Implementation of Row-Level Security (RLS) and Role-Based Access Control (RBAC).</li>
    <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Secure JWT-based authentication with short-lived tokens and httpOnly cookies.</li>
    <li><strong>Backups:</strong> Daily automated backups stored within the EU (Frankfurt) with high availability.</li>
    <li><strong>Incident Response:</strong> Formalized internal runbooks for rapid security incident containment and remediation.</li>
    <li><strong>Employee Access:</strong> Strict adherence to the "Minimum Necessary Access" principle for internal systems.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Sub-Processors</h2>
  <p>
    Passr utilizes the sub-processors listed in our <a href="/legal/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. Passr ensures that all sub-processors are bound by data protection obligations equivalent to those in this DPA.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Notification:</strong> Passr will provide the Customer with at least 30 days' notice before adding any new sub-processors that will process Customer personal data, providing the Customer the opportunity to object on legitimate grounds.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Data Subject Rights</h2>
  <p>
    Passr shall assist the Customer, taking into account the nature of the processing, by implementing appropriate technical and organizational measures for the fulfillment of the Customer's obligation to respond to requests for exercising data subject rights (access, deletion, portability). Passr commits to responding to Customer inquiries regarding such requests within <strong>72 hours</strong>.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Data Breach Notification</h2>
  <p>
    In accordance with Article 33 of the GDPR, Passr will notify the Customer without undue delay, and in any event within <strong>72 hours</strong>, after becoming aware of a personal data breach affecting the Customer's personal data.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Deletion on Termination</h2>
  <p>
    Upon termination of the subscription and following the 30-day "Data Escrow" export period, Passr shall delete all Customer personal data from its production systems within 30 days, unless EU or member state law requires continued storage.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Audit Rights</h2>
  <p>
    The Customer may request, no more than once per year, evidence of Passr's compliance with its obligations under this DPA. Such requests will be satisfied through the provision of security audit summaries or third-party certifications.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Governing Law</h2>
  <p>
    This DPA shall be governed by the same jurisdiction as the Passr Terms of Service (Estonia).
  </p>

  <h2 style="margin-top: 80px; border-bottom: none;">DPA EXECUTION SECTION</h2>
  
  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 40px; margin-top: 24px; padding-top: 24px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
    <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--color-metal); text-transform: uppercase;">
      <p style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-void); margin-bottom: 24px;">DATA CONTROLLER (CUSTOMER)</p>
      <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1); padding-bottom: 4px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Signature:</div>
      <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1); padding-bottom: 4px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Name:</div>
      <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1); padding-bottom: 4px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Title:</div>
      <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1); padding-bottom: 4px;">Date:</div>
    </div>
    <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--color-metal); text-transform: uppercase;">
      <p style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-void); margin-bottom: 24px;">DATA PROCESSOR (PASSR)</p>
      <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1); padding-bottom: 4px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Signature:</div>
      <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1); padding-bottom: 4px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Name: HISAKO TECHNOLOGIES OÜ</div>
      <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1); padding-bottom: 4px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Title: COMPLIANCE OFFICER</div>
      <div style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1); padding-bottom: 4px;">Date: APRIL 24, 2026</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p style="margin-top: 48px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; text-align: center; color: var(--color-metal); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">
    To execute this DPA, email <a href="mailto:legal@passr.eu">legal@passr.eu</a> with your company name and VAT number. We will return a countersigned copy within 2 business days.
  </p>

</Legal>
